Key concepts and areas of study: information environment, communication processes and elements, communication models, roles of journalists and public relations specialists, media content, construction of reality, media texts, myths, collective identities, media and power, media theories, media's role in society, media and politics, media and markets, audience studies, new media, media technologies and society, functional analysis, media organisations.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Students know and are familiar with the key concepts and vocabulary of the media and communication studies. Students have an overview of the theoretical and empirical research traditions of the media and communication work.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  General skills: are familiar with theoretical and empirical vocabulary and key ideas and overviews of media theories and empirics. They can understand the key problems of the communication research. 
Specific skills:
- have skills and experience for independent work 
- have very basic skills of interviewing
- have basic skills of individual and group research projects
- have skills to conduct some critical analysis of everyday media - reading and analysing news, understanding social representation of media and media functions and analysing of advertisements.
